UML:TaggedValue.value: SIG3D: Permanently installed parts of the building's outer shell which are accessory for the building structure including loggia, dormer, etc. Doors and windows are modeled by the corresponding CityGML classes.
SIG3D: Classification of BuildingInstallation as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Specified function of BuildingInstallation as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Actual usage of BuildingInstallation as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 solid geometry of BuildingInstallation.
SISIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 implicit representation of BuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Relation between Building or BuildingPart and BuildingInstallation
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD3 implicit representation of BuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD2 solid geometry of BuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD3 solid geometry of BuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Relation between BuildingInstallation and BoundarySurface. The boundary surfaces are part of BuildingInstallation's exterior shell either oriented inwards or outwards.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD2 implicit representation of BuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Abstract superclass of boundary surfaces of Building, BuildingPart, Room and BuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Relation between IntBuildingInstallation and BoundarySurface
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD3 surface geometry of AbstractBoundarySurface.
SIG3D: Relation between Room and BoundarySurface. The boundary surfaces are part of Room's exterior shell either oriented inwards or outwards.
SIG3D: Relation between BoundarySurface and AbstractOpening. The AbstractOpening object belongs to the BoundarySurface object. The geometry of both objects must not overlap.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 surface geometry of AbstractBoundarySurface.
SIG3D: Relation between Building or BuildingPart and AbstractBoundarySurface. The boundary surfaces are part of the building's or building part's exterior shell either oriented inwards or outwards.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD2 surface geometry of AbstractBoundarySurface.
ISO 6707-1: Construction for closing an opening intended primarily for access or egress or both.
SIG3D: Relation between Door and Address
SIG3D: Abstract super class of Window and Door
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD3 surface geometry of Door or Window.
SIG3D: Relation to LOD4 implicit geometry of Door and Window.
SIG3D: Relation to LOD3 implicit geometry of Door and Window.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 surface geometry of Door or Window.
SIG3D: Exterior, lower boundary surface of a building , building part or building installation bounded by air.
SIG3D: Exterior, lower boundary surface of a building , building part or building installation bounded by soil or water.
SIG3D: Lower boundary surface of a room, covering the lower limit of a room.
SIG3D: Exterior, upper boundary surface of a building, building part or building installation, whose primary function is to protect from the effects of weather.

SIG3D: A free-standing, self-supporting construction that is roofed, usually walled, and can be entered by humans and is normally designed to stand permanently in one place. It is intended for human occupancy (for example: a place of work or recreation), habitation and/or shelter of humans, animals or things.
SIG3D: Overhead boundary surface of a room, covering the upper limit of a room.
SIG3D: A Room represents a volume bounded actually or theoretically. Rooms are volumes that provide for certain functions within a building (cf. bSI).
SIG3D: Classification of Room as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Function of Room as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Usage of Room as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 surface geometry of Building or BuildingPart.
SIG3D: Relation between Building or BuildingPart and Room
SIG3D: Relation between Room and BuildingFurniture
SIG3D: Relation between Room and IntBuildingInstallation
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 solid geometry of Room.
SIG3D: Permanently installed parts of the buildings interior which are accessory for the building and for rooms. Doors and windows are modeled by the corresponding CityGML classes.
SIG3D: Classification of IntBuildingInstallation as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Specified function of IntBuildingInstallation as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Actual usage of IntBuildingInstallation as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 solid geometry of IntBuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 implicit representation of IntBuildingInstallation.
SIG3D: Relation between Building or BuildingPart and IntBuildingInstallation
SIG3D: Exterior or interior boundary surface providing virtual boundaries, typically used to seal holes in volumetric objects.
SIG3D: Exterior, lateral boundary surface of a building , building part, or building installation.
SIG3D: Lateral boundary surface of a room, covering the lateral limit of a room.
SIG3D: Abstract superclass of Building and BuildingPart.
SIG3D: Classification of Building or BuildingPart as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Specified function of Building or BuildingPart as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Actual usage of Building or BuildingPart as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Year of completion of this Building or BuildingPart.
SIG3D: Year of demolition of this Building or BuildingPart.
bSI: Basic configuration of the roof in terms of the different roof shapes.
SIG3D: Measured or calculated distance between the highest point od the roof construction and the lowest point of the terrain intersection of the building.
SIG3D: Number of storeys mainly above ground.
SIG3D: Number of storeys mainly below ground.
SIG3D: List of heights for each storey above ground.
SIG3D: List of heights for each storey below ground.
SIG3D: Representation of a Building or BuildingPart roof edge as GML MultiSurface with constant z-coordinate.
SIG3D: Relation to intersection curve(s) between a LOD4 Building or BuildingPart and a terrain (LOD1 or LOD2 or LOD3 or LOD4).

SIG3D: Relation to intersection curve(s) between a LOD3 Building or BuildingPart and a terrain (LOD1 or LOD2 or LOD3 or LOD4).
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD1 solid geometry of Building or BuildingPart.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD3 curve geometry of Building or BuildingPart, used to represent special objects like antenna, railings, ....
SIG3D: Relation between Building having BuildingPart or BuildingPart having BuildingPart
SIG3D: Representation of a Building or BuildingPart footprint as GML MultiSurface with constant z-coordinate.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD1 surface geometry of Building or BuildingPart.Geometrically, the LOD1 solid geometry and surface geometry are identical.
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 solid geometry of Building or BuildingPart.
SIG3D: Relation to intersection curve(s) between a LOD1 Building or BuildingPart and a terrain (LOD1 or LOD2 or LOD3 or LOD4).

SIG3D: Relation between Building or BuildingPart and Address
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD2 curve geometry of Building or BuildingPart, used to represent special objects like antennae, railings, ....
SIG3D: Relation to a LOD4 curve geometry of Building or BuildingPart, used to represent special objects like antenna, railings, ....
SIG3D: A BuildingPart is a sub-division of a Building that is homogeneous related to its physical, functional, or temporal aspects and may be considered as a Building.
SIG3D: Construction for closing an opening in a wall or roof, primarily intended to admit light and/or provide ventilation (cf. ISO 6707).
SIG3D: Equipment for occupant use, usually not fixed to the building (cf. ISO 6707-1) .
SIG3D: Classification of BuildingFurniture as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Specified function of BuildingFurniture as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
SIG3D: Actual usage of BuildingFurniture as given by the relevant national regulations, information communities, or specific applications.
